data.title: Carroll County Chamber of Commerce
data.meta_description: Connect with Carroll County Chamber of Commerce for business growth and event updates. Discover agricultural and historical sites, recreation, and community events. Boost site traffic with engaging posts.
data.text:
We are here to serve the businesses of our region by connecting them to area residents, visitors and other businesses, supporting and enhancing both our vibrant local economy and our outstanding quality of life.

Carroll County

Welcome to Carroll County! Carroll County lies in the heart of a rich agricultural section of the state in north central Missouri. According to the 2010 Census, Carroll County has a population of 8,319, with Carrollton holding the county seat. We are located approximately 75 miles northeast of Kansas City and at the intersection of U.S. highways 65 and 24.

Carrollton has a wonderful museum and historical society, quaint shops, delicious restaurants, a 9-hole private Country Club Golf Course, Carroll County Area YMCA, and a new aquatic center. We also have parks, lakes and places to hunt throughout the county to enjoy rural recreation, as well as several annual community events to fit the interests of the young and the old.
